  <static seed="2566" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Exponents/exponentsMultiplication20.pg">
    <statement><p>Use the properties of exponents to simplify the expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(r^{3}\right)^{2}}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="12" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>r^{6}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We <em>multiply</em> the exponents as follows: <me>\begin{aligned}
           \left(r^{3}\right)^{2}\amp =r^{3\cdot2}\\
                             \amp =r^{6}
       \end{aligned}</me></p>
</solution>
